01:08:39,998 --> 01:08:42,432
Somebody hit me with a cricket bat.

900
01:08:42,634 --> 01:08:43,999
Ah.

901
01:08:46,171 --> 01:08:48,799
- This is a new type of regulator...
- Shove it up your ass.

902
01:08:48,973 --> 01:08:51,237
- All right, we're good to go.
- Ready, darling?

903
01:08:51,409 --> 01:08:53,274
Drop dead.

904
01:08:54,212 --> 01:08:56,703
This is just like the old days, huh?

905
01:09:28,079 --> 01:09:29,842
Hello, darling.

906
01:09:31,216 --> 01:09:32,740
Drink?

907
01:09:34,786 --> 01:09:36,117
I have one.

908
01:10:46,024 --> 01:10:47,855
You know what else
is really bugging me?

909
01:10:48,626 --> 01:10:49,991
No.

910
01:10:50,161 --> 01:10:54,393
Please, tell us. Because I may personally
drop dead from disappointment...

911
01:10:54,566 --> 01:10:58,764
...if I don't find out the 700-millionth thing
about life on planet Earth...

912
01:10:58,937 --> 01:11:00,598
...that is bugging you.

913
01:11:01,172 --> 01:11:02,537
Well, this is fun.

914
01:11:02,707 --> 01:11:04,140
No, listen.

915
01:11:04,776 --> 01:11:08,337
If I am the Dutch frigate
stuck on a reef in a dead calm...

916
01:11:08,513 --> 01:11:11,573
<i>...in the same cove
the Aurelia sank three years earlier...</i>

917
01:11:11,749 --> 01:11:15,947
...in less than 30 feet
of the clearest water in the world...

918
01:11:16,855 --> 01:11:20,723
Then how come I can't see her?

919
01:11:24,896 --> 01:11:26,921
Because she isn't there.

920
01:11:29,367 --> 01:11:30,493
Yeah, I don't know.

921
01:11:30,668 --> 01:11:34,627
No, no, no. Sebastian specifically said
that's where she sank.

922
01:11:34,806 --> 01:11:36,637
- And he said it.
- Yeah.

923
01:11:36,808 --> 01:11:41,074
My dear children, your entire theory
is predicated on the proposition...

924
01:11:41,246 --> 01:11:46,013
...that Sebastian lied about everything he
could to prevent the ship being found.

925
01:11:46,184 --> 01:11:50,314
So why on Earth would
he tell the truth about where she sank?

926
01:11:51,322 --> 01:11:54,519
<i>I mean, it seems to me that
the Aurelia can't be in the cove...</i>

927
01:11:54,692 --> 01:11:58,128
...for the simple reason that
that's where Sebastian said she was.

928
01:12:13,611 --> 01:12:14,737
Sorry to disturb.

929
01:12:14,913 --> 01:12:17,609
We've had to move to the lee side
on account of the storm.

930
01:12:17,782 --> 01:12:19,807
She won't fit in the marina?

931
01:12:19,984 --> 01:12:23,613
Afraid not. A taxi will take you
to the beach on the north end.

932
01:12:23,788 --> 01:12:26,780
- Call, we'll pick you up on the launch.
- Better safe than sorry.

933
01:12:26,958 --> 01:12:28,391
Sir.

