01:12:29,093 --> 01:12:31,994
I've grown rather fond of not sinking.

935
01:12:32,196 --> 01:12:34,221
Ugh. Don't even say that.

936
01:12:34,399 --> 01:12:37,334
Oh, it would be a shame
to lose the art collection.

937
01:12:37,669 --> 01:12:38,693
Or Gemma's shoes.

938
01:12:39,604 --> 01:12:43,233
Especially because we're so close
to shore, you know?

939
01:12:47,078 --> 01:12:48,170
Oh, my God.

940
01:12:50,081 --> 01:12:51,548
What?

941
01:12:51,950 --> 01:12:53,178
Oh, my God, of course.

942
01:12:53,351 --> 01:12:55,012
Of course what?

943
01:12:57,221 --> 01:12:59,746
You are a genius.

944
01:13:01,593 --> 01:13:02,753
Stefan.

945
01:13:03,194 --> 01:13:05,287
- Stefan.
- Yes.

946
01:13:05,630 --> 01:13:08,224
Why did you pick the north beach?

947
01:13:08,733 --> 01:13:11,861
I didn't. It's the only beach on the
island not blocked by the reef.

948
01:13:12,637 --> 01:13:15,765
Yes. Yes. He ran her aground.

949
01:13:15,940 --> 01:13:17,601
What are you so happy about?

950
01:13:17,775 --> 01:13:20,300
- He ran her aground.
- What?

951
01:13:20,478 --> 01:13:26,178
To save the Dowry. Sebastian ran
the whole goddamn thing aground.

952
01:13:27,485 --> 01:13:30,943
Bet you $ 1000 I find something
between here and that beach.

953
01:13:31,122 --> 01:13:32,851
